(555, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Modern Languages & Cultures  Chinese', '17483', 'CHI 101', 'ELEMENTARY CHINESE I', 6, 5, 'This 6-credit course is designed for beginners of Chinese.  It introduces students to the sounds, basic sentence structures, and the writing system of Mandarin Chinese.  Pinyin, the phonetic translation system, is taught and required throughout the course.  Emphasis will be on developing listening and speaking skills as well as building a vocabulary based on 400 ideographic characters.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
