(788, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Clinical and Social Sciences in Psychology', '21898', 'CSP 377', 'EXPLORING RESEARCH IN FAMILY PSYCHOLOGY', 4, 5, 'Provides guided, direct, research experiences in investigating the interplay between family relationships and children’s social and emotional development. Emphasis is placed on gaining knowledge in translating theories (e.g., family systems theory) into empirically testable hypotheses and designing research methods and techniques to test predictions.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
(789, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Clinical and Social Sciences in Psychology', '21903', 'CSP 383', 'MORAL DEVELOPMENT', 4, 5, 'This seminar focuses on the psychological study of moral development. Different theoretical approaches to morality and related empirical research are discussed. The primary focus is from a developmental psychology perspective, but philosophicaland educational issues also are considered.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
