(802, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Clinical and Social Sciences in Psychology', '86686', 'CSP 575', 'PSYCHOPATHOLOGY I', 3, 5, 'Examines psychopathology of childhood and adulthood from a developmental perspective that encompasses the study of both normal and abnormal development. Topics covered include: taxonomic, definitional, and epidemiological issues; mental retardation; autism; child maltreatment; affective disorders; schizophrenia; resilience; and ethical considerations in conducting research.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
