(1033, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Economics', '24474', 'ECO 502', 'DISCRETE CHOICE MODELS', 3, 5, 'This course focuses on discrete choice models with applications in applied microeconomics fields, such as public, labor, education, health, and urban economics. Topics covered include static discrete choice models; models of sorting and spillovers; and dynamic single-agent models. In addition to identification and estimation, the course will have a heavy emphasis on programming.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
(1034, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Economics', '24483', 'ECO 504', 'TOPICS IN APPLIED MICRO', 3, 5, 'The course will discuss methods and topics broadly linked by intergenerational mobility. We will also try to construct a reasonable framework for understanding various methods employed by the applied literature using specific papers as examples.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
