(1281, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Modern Languages & Cultures  French', '27802', 'FR 101', 'ELEMENTARY FRENCH I', 4, 5, 'French 101 is an introductory language course.  Students learn fundamentals of grammar, and pronunciation in the context of French culture.  Emphasis is on developing communicating skills, principally speaking but also including listening, reading and writing.  There is an obligatory recitation section twice a week in addition to the main class and the work in the multimedia center. NO AUDITS', 'No prerequisite specified'),
