(2088, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Psychology', '40017', 'PSY 101', 'INTRODUCTION TO PSYCHOLOGY', 4, 5, 'Is a balanced and integrated survey of psychology with coverage of both social and natural science domains.  Sections of PSY 101 vary, but most consist of lectures, readings, discussions, and demonstrations.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
(2089, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Psychology', '40026', 'PSY 101', 'INTRODUCTION TO PSYCHOLOGY', 4, 5, 'Is a balanced and integrated survey of psychology with coverage of both social and natural science domains.  Sections of PSY 101 vary, but most consist of lectures, readings, discussions, and demonstrations.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
(2090, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Psychology', '40034', 'PSY 110', 'NEURAL FOUNDATIONS OF BEHAVIOR', 4, 5, 'Introduces the structure and organization of the brain, and its role in perception, movement, thinking, and other behavior. Topics include the brain as a special kind of computer, localization of function, effects of brain damage and disorders, differences between human and animal brains, sex differences, perception and control of movement, sleep, regulation of body states and emotions, and development and aging.', 'None'),
(2091, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Psychology', '40080', 'PSY 111', 'FOUNDATIONS OF COGNITIVE SCIENCE', 4, 5, 'Introduces the organization of mental processes underlying cognition and behavior. Topics include perception, language, learning, memory, and intelligence. This course integrates knowledge of cognition generated from the field of cognitive psychology with findings from artificial intelligence and cognitive neuroscience.', 'None'),
(2092, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Psychology', '40099', 'PSY 151', 'PERCEPTION & ACTION', 4, 5, 'Explores how the biology of our senses shapes perceptual experiences of reality. Emphasizes sense of sight primarily and hearing secondarily. An important theme is that our sensory systems play a crucial role in the execution of coordinated movements of our bodies, as we navigate in, and interact with, the environment.', 'BCS 110 or BCS 111'),
(2093, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Psychology', '40103', 'PSY 152', 'LANGUAGE & PSYCHOLINGUISTICS', 4, 5, 'Overviews the nature and processing of human languages, including comparisons between language and animal communication systems, the biological bases of human language, and the cognitive mechanisms used in producing, understanding, and learning language.', 'BCS 110 or BCS 111 or LIN 110'),
(2094, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Psychology', '40112', 'PSY 171', 'SOCIAL AND EMOTIONAL DEVELOPMENT', 4, 5, 'An examination of the interpersonal, emotional, cognitive, and environmental factors that influence children\'s social and emotional development from early infancy through late adolescence.', 'No prerequisite specified');
