(2292, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Sustainability', '43466', 'SUS 473', 'MASTER\'S CAPSTONE DEVELOPMNT', 1, 5, 'No description yet', 'No prerequisite specified'),
(2293, 1, 'Fall 2019', 'Sustainability', '43479', 'SUS 488', 'INTRO TO ENERGY SYSTEMS', 4, 5, 'The goal of this course is to provide a succinct introduction to the different means ofproducing energy. The first and second laws of thermodynamics are reviewed tointroduce the concepts of conservation of energy and efficiency. Then these conceptsare applied to a number of different energy technologies, including wind, hydroelectric,geothermal, fuel cells, biomass, and nuclear. For each type of technology, a technicalintroduction is given so that the student will understand the governing scientificprinciples.', 'No prerequisite specified'),
